h when i began to see /ooc comments to the effect of &quot;paying 11pp to unlock the door in the bank&quot;...much to my amusement i discovered that someone had followed somebody else into the locked room behind the bankers, and had gotten stuck inside.  Apparently this fellow was so unpopular tat people were auctioning money to pay off rogues to NOT let him out.  Being a locksmith in RL, this situation comes up dailey many many times, so that side of me overrode the roguish desire to see the guy panic a bit more, so i ran to E FP to train up my lockpicking skill with the 25 practices i had been saving.  Of course, upon my return he had been released from the room, and my skill was still not high enough to pick the lock.  In any case, it was the first time i had seen anyone request the help of a rogue, EVER.  I hope to see more of this with the expansion, and i pray that I see the phrase &quot;can someone with lockpicks open this door for me?&quot; alot more often.....and for your info, Locksmiths in RL make a killing letting people in their cars, houses, etc... just remember to charge alot of money for this service:) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uhoophalflingsbane.showPublicProfile>Hoop Halflingsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/21/00 9:53:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...only a rogue could appreciate this (or a locksmith)</span><hr size=1> Yeah, lockpicking is the only thing I've ever been ask for (a whopping 2 times now).  Both regarded the Bank door in Freeport. <p>Hoop Halflingsbane, Mithaniel Marr<BR>
